Research Abstract

Enhancing SEL in Urban Schools through Culturally Responsive Positive Action

This study evaluates a culturally adapted version of the Positive Action curriculum, tailored for students' identities through real-life scenarios, anime-style affirmations, and creative rap/R&B products. Results demonstrate measurable gains in emotion regulation among 5th-grade participants.

Sample Size n = 8
Dosage 30 Sessions
Primary Gain Emotion Reg.
Adaptations
  • Identity Mapping: Curriculum names and scenarios adjusted for local cultural relevance.
  • Creative Output: Rap/R&B songwriting replaced standard written assessments.
  • Visual Anchors: "Watermark" temporary tattoos used as physical affirmations.
